re indeed very powerful and helpful. But there is one thing that&#xA0;Salesforce&#xA0;users often forget:&#xA0;list views&#xA0;and kanban.</p>
</div></div></div> <div data-v-3cb16c5a><div class="h-[24px] lg:h-[52px]" data-v-3cb16c5a></div> <div class="max-w-screen-lg bg-lavender mx-auto px-[16px] py-[20px] mb-[32px] md:px-[52px] lg:py-[74px] lg:rounded-[10px] lg:mb-[48px]" data-v-3cb16c5a><div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-md flex flex-col space-y-[16px]"><h2 class="font-700 text-charcoal text-[24px] leading-[32px] md:text-[34px] md:leading-[40px] md:tracking-[0.25px] lg:text-[40px] lg:leading-[48px] lg:tracking-[0px]">Contents</h2> <div></div> <a href="#usingsalesforcelistviews" class="cursor-pointer font-400 text-charcoal/70 inline-block text-[14px] leading-[24px] tracking-[0.1px] md:text-[16px] md:tracking-[0.15px]">1. Using Salesforce List Views
    </a></div></div></div> <div class="flair-container" data-v-3cb16c5a><div data-v-3cb16c5a><!----> <div data-v-3cb16c5a><article class="blog-markdown mx-auto max-w-screen-md prose prose-hr:h-[8px] prose-hr:m-0 prose-hr:border-none prose-headings:my-0 prose-headings:font-700 prose-headings:text-charcoal prose-h1:mb-[32px] prose-h1:mt-[48px] prose-h1:text-[34px] prose-h1:leading-[40px] prose-h1:tracking-[0.25px] md:prose-h1:text-[48px] md:prose-h1:leading-[56px] md:prose-h1:tracking-[0px] lg:prose-h1:text-[60px] lg:prose-h1:leading-[72px] prose-h2:text-[24px] prose-h2:leading-[32px] prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h2:mt-[48px] prose-h2:mb-[24px] md:prose-h2:text-[34px] md:prose-h2:leading-[40px] md:prose-h2:tracking-[0.25px] lg:prose-h2:text-[40px] lg:prose-h2:leading-[48px] lg:prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h3:text-[20px] prose-h3:leading-[32px] prose-h3:tracking-[0.15px] prose-h3:mb-[20px] md:prose-h3:text-[24px] md:prose-h3:leading-[32px] md:prose-h3:tracking-[0px] prose-p:m-0 prose-p:font-500 prose-p:text-charcoal prose-p:text-[14px] prose-p:leading-[24px] prose-p:tracking-[0.1px] prose-p:mb-[20px] md:prose-p:text-[16px] md:prose-p:leading-[32px] md:prose-p:tracking-[0.15px] prose-a:text-blue prose-strong:font-700 prose-blockquote:border-none prose-blockquote:relative prose-p:before:content-[] prose-blockquote:not-italic prose-blockquote:m-0 prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_16px] md:prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_26px] prose-blockquote:before:absolute prose-blockquote:before:inset-0 prose-blockquote:before:w-[4px] prose-blockquote:before:bg-blue prose-blockquote:before:rounded-full prose-blockquote:before:left-0 md:prose-blockquote:before:w-[6px] prose-ol:pl-[16px] prose-ol:mb-[20px] prose-ol:list-decimal md:prose-ol:pl-[26px] prose-li:marker:proportional-nums prose-ul:pl-[16px] prose-ul:mb-[20px] prose-ul:list-disc md:prose-ul:pl-[26px] prose-li:font-500 prose-li:text-charcoal prose-li:text-[16px] prose-li:leading-[32px] prose-li:m-0 prose-li:p-0 prose-table:table-fixed prose-table:border-[0px] prose-table:text-charcoal prose-table:text-[14px] prose-table:leading-[24px] md:prose-table:text-[16px] prose-tr:grid prose-tr:divide-y-[3px] prose-tr:divide-lavender prose-tr:border-[0px] sm:prose-tr:border-[3px] sm:prose-tr:border-lavender sm:prose-tr:table-row prose-td:p-[32px] sm:prose-td:border-[3px] sm:prose-td:border-lavender prose-th:p-[32px] empty:prose-th:hidden sm:empty:prose-th:table-cell sm:prose-th:border-[3px] sm:prose-th:border-lavender prose-thead:border-[3px] prose-thead:border-lavender prose-tbody:border-[3px] prose-tbody:border-lavender prose-tbody:divide-y-[3px] prose-tbody:divide-lavender"><h2 id="usingsalesforcelistviews">Using Salesforce List Views</h2>
<p>You can easily create a different representation or segment data with&#xA0;list views.</p>
<p>Some examples of how you can use&#xA0;list views include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Displaying all employees who are starting next month.</li>
<li>A list of pending absences.</li>
<li>Direct reports of a specific manager.</li>
</ul>
<p>All of these views can easily be achieved with&#xA0;Salesforce&#xA0;list views.</p>
<p>Let's try with the example of employees starting next month:</p>
<h3>Step 1: Employee Object Tab</h3>
<p>In your&#xA0;Salesforce&#xA0;Lightning&#xA0;Experience, open an Employee&#xA0;object&#xA0;Tab:</p>
